<section id="how-we-use-it">
  <h2>
    <span class="section-icon">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
    </span>
    How We Use It
  </h2>
  
  <p>Your information serves one purpose: helping you grow. Here's what that looks like:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Personalized coaching:</strong> Remembering your goals, struggles, and wins so every conversation builds on the last</li>
    <li><strong>Continuity:</strong> Picking up where we left off, whether it's been a day or a month</li>
    <li><strong>Better service:</strong> Understanding what works so we can keep improving</li>
    <li><strong>Reaching you:</strong> Sending updates about your account (only with your permission for marketing)</li>
    <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Protecting against fraud and keeping the service secure</li>
  </ul>
  
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>What we'll never do:</strong>
    <p>Sell your data. Show you ads based on your conversations. Share your story with anyone who doesn't need it to help us serve you.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="keeping-it-safe">
  <h2>
    <span class="section-icon">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
    </span>
    Keeping It Safe
  </h2>
  
  <p>Trust is earned. Here's how we protect yours:</p>
  
  <h3>Encryption Everywhere</h3>
  <p>Your conversations are encrypted in transit (as they travel to us) and at rest (when they're stored). Even our team can't read your conversations without specific, logged authorization.</p>
  
  <h3>Industry Standards</h3>
  <p>We use the same security practices trusted by banks and healthcare providers. Regular audits, access controls, and monitoring keep your data protected.</p>
  
  <h3>Minimal Access</h3>
  <p>Only the systems that need your data to serve you can access it. Our team operates on a strict need-to-know basis.</p>
  
  <h3>Continuous Improvement</h3>
  <p>Security isn't a destination—it's a practice. We regularly review and upgrade our protections as technology evolves.</p>
</section>

<section id="who-sees-what">
  <h2>
    <span class="section-icon">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
    </span>
    Who Sees What
  </h2>
  
  <p>We work with trusted partners to make Ferni possible. They're bound by strict contracts to protect your information:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cloud infrastructure:</strong> Secure servers that store and process your data</li>
    <li><strong>AI providers:</strong> The language models that power our conversations</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Tools that help us understand how to improve (never linked to your personal conversations)</li>
    <li><strong>Payment processors:</strong> If you're a subscriber, they handle payment securely</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>These partners only see what they need to do their job. They can't use your data for their own purposes, and they're held to the same standards we hold ourselves to.</p>
  
  <h3>When We Might Have to Share</h3>
  <p>In rare cases, we may need to share information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>To comply with valid legal requests</li>
    <li>To protect safety (yours, ours, or others')</li>
    <li>If Ferni is acquired (your privacy protections would transfer)</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p>We'll always tell you if we're compelled to share your data, unless we're legally prohibited from doing so.</p>
</section>

<section id="your-control">
  <h2>
    <span class="section-icon">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 22a10 10 0 1 0 0-20 10 10 0 0 0 0 20z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg>
    </span>
    Your Control
  </h2>
  
  <p>Your data belongs to you. Here's what you can do with it:</p>
  
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access:</strong> See what we have stored about you</li>
    <li><strong>Correct:</strong> Fix anything that's wrong</li>
    <li><strong>Export:</strong> Download your conversation history</li>
    <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Request we remove your data entirely</li>
    <li><strong>Opt out:</strong> Stop marketing emails anytime</li>
  </ul>
  
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Deleting your data:</strong>
    <p>If you ask us to delete everything, we will—but we'll lose the ability to remember your story. You'd be starting fresh. Some information may be retained for legal compliance, but it won't be used for coaching.</p>
  </div>
  
  <p>To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:privacy@ferni.ai">privacy@ferni.ai</a>. We'll respond within 30 days.</p>
</section>

<section id="special-cases">
  <h2>
    <span class="section-icon">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
    </span>
    Special Cases
  </h2>
  
  <h3>Children</h3>
  <p>Ferni is designed for adults. We don't knowingly collect information from anyone under 13. If you believe a child has used our service, contact us immediately.</p>
  
  <h3>International Users</h3>
  <p>We're based in the United States, and your data is processed here. If you're using Ferni from elsewhere, your information crosses borders—but our protections travel with it.</p>
  
  <h3>California Residents</h3>
  <p>You have additional rights under the CCPA, including knowing what we collect, deleting your data, and opting out of "sales" (which we don't do anyway). Same email: <a href="mailto:privacy@ferni.ai">privacy@ferni.ai</a>.</p>
  
  <h3>European Users</h3>
  <p>Under GDPR, you have rights to access, rectification, erasure, and data portability. We process your data based on legitimate interest (providing the service you've requested) and consent (for optional features).</p>
</section>

